Q.  (Inaudible)?
MI-HYUN KIM: No, actually, I don't care about the cut.  I just want to try to get to the top 10 or 5.  I don't want to think about the cut.

Q.  (Inaudible)?
MI-HYUN KIM: Yeah, and I shoot maybe 4 or 5 under, and then the second day, it was very hot that time.  I went to the hospital that day.

Q.  (Inaudible)?
MI-HYUN KIM: No, no, no. 

Q.  (Inaudible)?
MI-HYUN KIM: 99.

Q.  Can you tell us about your round today?  5 under is a pretty good score.  Did you see it coming?
MI-HYUN KIM: Yesterday it was fun.  I played with the Korean guys.  It was very fun.  I just don't worry about the front 9, par 3, number 4 and 7, because the greens are tough and the affairs are long.  I made a birdie.  It was good for me. 
